```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Start([Start Main Loop]) --> GetTarget{Get Target}
    GetTarget -->|"Target is Rope Top"| MoveToRope[Align X with Rope]
    MoveToRope --> CheckAlign{Aligned?}
    CheckAlign -->|"No (dx > 5px)"| MoveToRope
    CheckAlign -->|"Yes"| StartClimb[Start Climb (Hold UP)]

    subgraph Climbing Loop [Hold UP Loop]
        CheckHeight{Reach Target Y?}
        CheckHeight -->|"Yes"| StopClimb[Release Keys]
        StopClimb --> Complete([Task Complete -> Next Node])
        
        CheckHeight -->|"No"| CheckDrift{X Drift > 5px?}
        
        CheckDrift -->|"No"| ContinueClimbing[Keep Holding UP]
        ContinueClimbing --> CheckHeight
        
        CheckDrift -->|"Yes (Monster Hit!)"| EmergencyStop[STOP CLIMBING!]
    end

    EmergencyStop --> ReleaseKeys[Release Keys]
    ReleaseKeys --> LoopRestart([End Action -> Main Loop Tick])
    
    LoopRestart --> GetTargetAgain{Main Loop: Get Target}
    GetTargetAgain -->|"Target is STILL Rope Top"| MoveToRope
    
    style EmergencyStop fill:#f96,stroke:#333
    style LoopRestart fill:#bbf,stroke:#333
    style StartClimb fill:#9f9,stroke:#333
```

### Potential Bug Analysis (Where it could fail):
1. **Infinite Knockback Loop**:
   - If a monster **Camp** (stays) at the rope bottom.
   - You Align -> Grab Rope -> Monster Hits you (Drift > 5px) -> Emergency Stop.
   - Main Loop Restarts -> Align -> Grab Rope -> Monster Hits you...
   - **Result**: Character gets stuck in an infinite "Grab-Hit-Drop" loop until the monster moves or dies. *(This is standard game behavior, hard to fix without killing the monster)*.

2. **Knockback onto "Wrong Platform"**:
   - If the monster hits you HARD and you land on a *different* platform (e.g., above or far below).
   - "Get Target" might still point to the OLD Rope Top.
   - If you are now closer to a *different* path node, the [PathPlanningTracker](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#85-94) needs to be smart enough to **Re-Calculate** (Recalculate Path).
   - **Current Logic**: [PathPlanningTracker](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#85-94) usually recalculates if "Off Path". If valid, it recovers.

3. **Drift Sensor Malfunction**:
   - If Vision is laggy and reports "Fake Drift".
   - Character stops climbing for no reason.
   - **Result**: "Stuttering" climb (Start-Stop-Start-Stop). Inefficient but eventually succeeds.
